          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search               This article does not cite any sources. Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. (October 2012) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)     Mahanagaram    Promotional Poster    Directed by T. K. Rajeev Kumar   Produced by M. Mani   Screenplay by Dennis Joseph   Story by Muttathu Varkey   Starring Mammootty Shanthi Krishna Murali Thilakan    Release dates  1992   Country India   Language Malayalam   Mahanagaram (Malayalam: മഹാനഗരം) is a 1992 Malayalam film directed by T. K. Rajeev Kumar and starring Mammootty in the lead role.[1]    Contents   1 Plot 2 Cast 3 References 4 External links    Plot[edit] Movie commences with a smuggling sequence.In which Chanthakkad Viswan tactically grabs the goods from customs and takes it to his clients. When he refuses their offer to join them as a partner the dispute starts. When he was driving back to his home town in Calicut, he was attacked by a bunch of criminals but he was saved by Chandrdas IPS who was on his to Calicut to take charge as the Asst.Police Commissioner.He took Viswan to hospital. And he introduced himself, which was quite a surprise for him.But Viswan framed himself as a farmer. Later he skipped from the hospital and met again with Chandradas and family with his broken wheels. They gone with him and took a visit ti Viswan's huest house in a beach. Ummaru kutti who was his so called manager drive them to their premises. Later they came to know that he was the son in law of Writer, a notorious land lord. The story slowly starts and goes in pace. In the next part, Chandradas realizes the hidden face of Viswam. Viswam informs Chandrdas about a smuggling deal, and Chandrdas takes them down. He get fame in no time. But the smuggling team was belonged to Writer. Before the questining the program starts Writer's hingemen finishes the prisoner. Chandradas was forced to obey him, in order to wash of the dirt. Viswan caught the murderer but Chandradas was igonore about the whole story. Viswam meets his ex- affair, Radhika. She is now the Asst Collector. Movie goesthrough some twists and tweaks at this moment. Meanwhile Chandradas's children gets kidnapped. And movie slowly reaches the climax. Cast[edit]  Mammootty as Chanthakkadu Viswan Thilakan Murali Shanthi Krishna Meenakumari K. P. A. C. Sunny Shivaji Augustine Zeenath T. P. Madhavan Kundara Johny T.S.Krishnan Biyon  References[edit]   ^ "Mahanagaram Film Details". malayalachalachithram. Retrieved 2014-09-28.    External links[edit]  Kottayam Kunjachan at the Internet Movie Database http://popcorn.oneindia.in/title/5783/kottayam-kunjachan.html Srikanth debuts in Malayalam      This article about a Malayalam film of the 1990s is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e                         Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Mahanagaram&oldid=714512949"          Categories: 1990 filmsIndian films1990s Malayalam-language films1990s action films1990s romantic comedy films1990s Malayalam-language film stubsHidden categories: Use dmy dates from November 2015Use Indian English from November 2015All Wikipedia articles written in Indian EnglishArticles lacking sources from October 2012All articles lacking sourcesAll stub articles            
